ion conceived as the set of fundamental political rules derived from the very nature of political regime and its historical development.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aConstitution, Legal Tradition, Political Thought, Rechtsstaat.1 aGórnisiewicz, Arkadiusz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGórnisiewicz, Arkadiusz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHörcher, Ferenc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJokubaitis, Alvydas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaczorowski, Paweł, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOsipov, Igor D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPietrzyk-Reeves, Dorota, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRzegocki, Arkady, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkrobacki, Waldemar A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmorgunov, Leonid V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzlachta, Bogdan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzlachta, Bogdan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUjazdowski, Kazimierz Michał, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb0 cEPUBz97831105821850 cprintz978311058191140uhttps://doi.org/1